ANTHRAX - ZAMBIA
****************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Sat, 29 Nov 1997 23:38:21 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@guttenberg.correionet.com.br>
Source: The Times of Zambia <times@zamnet.zm> and Africa News Online


Lusaka
Anthrax has broken out in Western Province, infecting more than 70 people
and over 200 animals, provincial veterinary officer Godffrey Bbalo said
yesterday.
Dr Bbalo said eight people have been admitted to Senanga Hospital from
Sibukali area with anthrax while more than 10 have been treated in Sikongo
area in Kalabo. More than 200 animals were reported to be infected with
the disease in the two areas, Dr Bbalo said.
--
Luiz Jacintho da Silva. M.D.
